    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-18T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-18T23:00:00-05:00" n="179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-19T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 19, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>732. Legation’s 731, August 19, 11 a.m.<note n="57" xml:id="d179fn57">Not
                        printed.</note> Following in part from Reuter, Nanking, August 16th: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Referring to reports of Russian incursions into China border districts,
                            Dr. Wang said that the Ministry so far had received no official reports
                            but added ‘We are determined to resist to the limit of our ability <pb
                                facs="0430" n="286" xml:id="pg_286"/> if these raids continue for
                            unless we are in the grip of the Communists or are conquered by them we
                            must fight our invaders and’ he said ‘China remains firm. The Russian
                            associate managers of the Chinese Eastern Railway cannot be reinstated
                            before the opening of negotiations. China’s only course is for the
                            entire nation to unite and resist Red imperialism or perish in the grip
                            of communism.’”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
